\n\n11,783.70%\n\n Key Events\n Mountain\n\n Advanced Chart\n\n Loading chart for GOOGL\n\n Chart does not reflect overnight price.\n\nNews headlines Alphabet Inc. (GOOGL) is experiencing mixed performance as it navigates a challenging market environment. Recent developments include a notable 2.8% increase in stock price amid broader market gains, while analysts project a 19.88% revenue increase for the next quarter.\n\n Alphabet Inc. (GOOGL) is experiencing mixed performance as it navigates a challenging market environment. Recent developments include a notable 2.8% increase in stock price amid broader market gains, while analysts project a 19.88% revenue increase for the next quarter.\n\n Updated 30m ago · Powered by Yahoo Scout\n View more\nPrevious Close 287.56\nOpen 290.83\nBid 297.40 x 100\nAsk 297.38 x 300\nDay's Range 290.41 - 300.52\n52 Week Range 140.53 - 349.00\nVolume 37,550,664\nAvg. Volume 34,545,572\nMarket Cap (intraday) 3.598T\nBeta (5Y Monthly) 1.11\nPE Ratio (TTM) 27.54\nEPS (TTM) 10.80\nEarnings Date (est.) Apr 23, 2026\nForward Dividend & Yield 0.84 (0.28%)\nEx-Dividend Date Mar 9, 2026\n1y Target Est 376.93\n\nAlphabet Inc. Overview Internet Content & Information / Communication Services\n\n Alphabet Inc. offers various products and platforms in the United States, Europe, the Middle East, Africa, the Asia-Pacific, Canada, and Latin America. It operates through Google Services, Google Cloud, and Other Bets segments. The Google Services segment provides products and services, including ads, Android, Chrome, devices, Gmail, Google Drive, Google Maps, Google Photos, Google Play, Search, and YouTube. It is also involved in the sale of apps and in-app purchases and digital content in Google Play and YouTube; and devices, as well as the provision of YouTube consumer subscription services, such as YouTube TV, YouTube Music and Premium, NFL Sunday Ticket, and Google One. The Google Cloud segment offers consumption-based fees and subscriptions for AI solutions, including AI infrastructure, Vertex AI platform, and Gemini enterprise. It also provides cybersecurity, and data and analytics services; Google Workspace that include cloud-based communication and collaboration tools for enterprises, such as Calendar, Gmail, Docs, Drive, and Meet; and other enterprise services. The Other Bets segment sells transportation and internet services. Alphabet Inc. was incorporated in 1998 and is headquartered in Mountain View, California.\n abc.xyz\n 190,820\n\nFull Time Employees\n\nDecember 31\n\nFiscal Year Ends\n\nCommunication Services\n\nSector\n\nInternet Content & Information\n\nIndustry\n\n More about Alphabet Inc.\n\nRecent News: GOOGL\n View More\n All News Earnings Calls Press Releases SEC Filings\n https://finance.yahoo.com/video/could-apples-next-50-years-of-success-lie-in-ai-foldable-phones-213744964.html Could Apple's next 50 years of success lie in AI, foldable phones? Yahoo Finance Video 8h ago\n\n https://finance.yahoo.com/news/morning-brief-stocks-roar-back-plus-our-giant-action-packed-q1-roundup-100033568.html Morning Brief: Stocks roar back, plus our giant, action-packed Q1 roundup Yahoo Finance 20h ago\n\n https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/stocks/articles/netflix-nflx-seeks-expand-nfl-055431759.html Netflix (NFLX) Seeks to Expand NFL Streaming Rights to Four Games Insider Monkey 26m ago\n\n https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/stocks/articles/nvidia-discount-tech-valuations-look-003132274.html Nvidia At A Discount? Tech Valuations Look Attractive And Mark Gibbens Says It's 'A Great Time to Get In' On PLTR, NVDA And GOOGL Benzinga 5h ago\n\n https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/stocks/articles/why-alphabet-inc-goog-outpaced-214502312.html Why Alphabet Inc. (GOOG) Outpaced the Stock Market Today Zacks 8h ago\n\n https://finance.yahoo.com/sectors/technology/articles/yuki-brings-real-time-cost-212600428.html Yuki Brings Real-Time Cost Optimization to BigQuery GlobeNewswire 8h ago\n\n https://finance.yahoo.com/sectors/t