ry Internet Content & Information\n\n SPOT Spotify Technology S.A.\n\n 475.99 -2.18%\n\n Mkt Cap 97.998B\n Industry Internet Content & Information\n\n PINS Pinterest, Inc.\n\n 17.62 -1.78%\n\n Mkt Cap 11.291B\n Industry Internet Content & Information\n\n DJT Trump Media & Technology Group Corp.\n\n 9.39 +1.40%\n\n Mkt Cap 2.599B\n Industry Internet Content & Information\n\n BIDU Baidu, Inc.\n\n 108.41 +0.17%\n\n Mkt Cap 36.887B\n Industry Internet Content & Information\n\n 0700.HK Tencent Holdings Limited\n\n 504.500 -0.79%\n\n Mkt Cap HKD 4.559T\n Industry Internet Content & Information\n\nCompany Insights: META\n\nFair Value\n\n Fair Value is the appropriate price for the shares of a company, based on its earnings and growth rate also interpreted as when P/E Ratio = Growth Rate. Estimated return represents the projected annual return you might expect after purchasing shares in the company and holding them over the default time horizon of 5 years, based on the EPS growth rate that we have projected. Learn more\n\n 629.86 Current\n\n /about/plans/select-plan/fair-value/?.done=%2Fquote%2FMETA%2Ffair-value%2F&ncid=100001111\n\nDividend Score\n\n The distribution of earnings a company pays back to its shareholders based off the company’s profits. Usually paid out on a quarterly basis in the form of cash or additional stocks.\n\n 0 Low\n\n Sector Avg.\n\n 100 High\n\n /about/plans/select-plan/dividends/?.done=%2Fquote%2FMETA%2Fdividends%2F&ncid=100001114\n\nHiring Score\n\n A company’s hiring trends in key indicators can indicate how well the company is doing in terms of growing the company and where they are currently prioritizing.\n\n 0 Low\n\n Sector Avg.\n\n 100 High\n\n /about/plans/select-plan/hiring-trends/?.done=%2Fquote%2FMETA%2Fhiring-trends%2F&ncid=100001113\n\nInsider Sentiment Score\n\n Vicker’s Insider Sentiment provides insights into trades made by insiders. This can be used to gain valuable insights and as a reflection of the prospect of the company based on insider trading.\n\n 0 Low\n\n Sector Avg.\n\n 100 High\n\n /about/plans/select-plan/insider-sentiment/?.done=%2Fquote%2FMETA%2Finsider-sentiment%2F&ncid=100001115\n\nResearch Reports: META\n View More\n### Meta: Muse Models May Just Be the Spark That the Firm Needed in AI Model Development\n Meta is the largest social media company in the world, boasting close to 4 billion monthly active users worldwide. The firm's \"Family of Apps,\" its core business, consists of Facebook, Instagram, Messenger, and WhatsApp. End users can leverage these applications for a variety of different purposes, from keeping in touch with friends to following celebrities and running digital businesses for free. Meta packages customer data, gleaned from its application ecosystem and sells ads to digital advertisers. While the firm has been investing heavily in its Reality Labs business, it remains a very small part of Meta’s overall sales. Rating Price Target Morningstar• 4 days ago /research/reports/MS_0P0000W3KZ_AnalystReport_1775686384000\n### Product-liability trial loss\n Meta Platforms operates the world's largest family of social networking websites, including the flagship Facebook site, Instagram, Facebook Messenger, WhatsApp, Reels, and Threads. The sites enable users to communicate with friends and family by posting content; to comment on the posts of others; to share photographs, website links, and videos; to message; and to play games. The company also partners with application developers to add functionality to the sites and allows users to pay for virtual goods and services through its Payments function. Meta's Superintelligence Labs is one of the pioneers in generative AI research and its Reality Labs segment develops and sells new computing form factors like virtual reality headsets and smart glasses. Meta derives about 63% of its revenue from outside the U.S. Rating Price Target Argus• 16 days ago /research/reports/ARGUS_3592_AnalystReport_1774609122000\n### The whiplash from the war-related remains in full force. The major stock\n The whiplash from the war-related remains in full force. The major stock indices fell between 1% and 2.4% on Thursday as gloom prevailed. But at the end of the day, President Trump announced he had, again, extended the deadline for additional military action, this time until April 6. Still, stocks have headed south more than they have headed north of late, and the technical condition of the market is weakening. The S&P 500 (SPX) has fallen below its 13-, 26-, and 40-week exponential moving averages (EMAs) for the first time since March of 2025 and the 13-week EMA is close to a bearish cross of the 26-week. The two shorter averages have rolled over and are heading lower, while the longer average has flattened. A technical sell signal would occur if the 13-week falls below both the 26- and 40-week EMAs and the 26-week declines below the 40-week EMA. Argus• 16 days ago /research/reports/ARGUS_46561_MarketSummary_1774608222000\n### Meta: Legal Headwinds Grow but We Think the Firm Can Weather the Storm; Maintaining $850 Fair Value\n Meta is the largest social media company in the world, boasting close to 4 billion monthly active users worldwide. The firm's \"Family of Apps,\" its core business, consists of Facebook, Instagram, Messenger, and WhatsApp. End users can leverage these applications for a variety of different purposes, from keeping in touch with friends to following celebrities and running digital businesses for free. Meta packages customer data, gleaned from its application ecosystem and sells ads to digital advertisers. While the firm has been investing heavily in its Reality Labs business, it remains a very small part of Meta’s overall sales. Rating Price Target Morningstar• 16 days ago /research/reports/MS_0P0000W3KZ_AnalystReport_1774576330000\n\n View More\n\nPeople Also Watch\n\n AMZN Amazon.com, Inc.\n\n 238.38 +2.02%\n\n /quote/AMZN/\n AAPL Apple Inc.\n\n 260.48 -0.00%\n\n /quote/AAPL/\n 